HEADWORD: Overtrade
<hw>O`ver*trade"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To trade
beyond one's capital; to buy goods beyond the means of paying for or
selling them; to overstock the market.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overtrading</ent>⟦br⟧
